  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The health_monthly view (source: sensor_readings) has dimensions: reading_date, vehicle_model, pit, alert_level. Measures: avg_health_score, avg_engine_temp, vehicle_count, critical_count, reading_count. The failure_monthly view (source: failure_events) has dimensions: event_month, vehicle_model, pit, failure_type. Measures: total_downtime, total_repair_cost, avg_rul, failure_count, high_risk_count. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. vehicle_id, vehicle_name).",
